			h3 #[strong Opening]
			p A chess opening refers to the initial moves of a chess game, they are often memorized by those who play a lot to avoid making mistakes.
			p It is important to remember that after Bob plays, Alice will play her turn and then Bob and so on. Playing first is an advantage because you can lead the direction of the game so winning furigoma has some importance. Bob plays the first move.
