			h2 Special Rules
			h3 Promotion
			p Pieces can only promote if they have the unpromoted face up. 
			p Gold and king are the only pieces which can't be promoted.
			h3 Drops
			p A player can either capture, move or drop a piece.
			p A piece that has been captured can be dropped onto a vacant square with its unpromoted face up.
			p Pieces can't be promoted when being dropped.
			h3 Promotion
			p Promotion is only possible if the piece is in the promotion zone or leaving it.
			p The promotion zone is the combination of the three furthest rows from the player.
			p When a piece is promoted, the piece is flipped over revealing the promoted piece.
			p A piece can not be unpromoted.
			p A pawn can not be dropped onto a column which already contains a pawn belonging to the same player.
			p A pawn can not be dropped to deliver checkmate.
			p A pawn can not be dropped on the last row.
			p A lance can not be dropped on the last two rows.
			p A piece may not be dropped or moved to a square from which it will have no valid moves regardless of which pieces surround it. 
			h2 Stalemate, draws and repetition
			p Stalemate is a board state where the player is unable to make a valid move and where the king isn't attacked, instead of being a draw like in western chess it is a loss for the one who can't move.
			p Both players can also agree on a draw.
